Chronic sleep deprivation can lead to concentration issues, poor mood, and heart problems.
A study showed that just five nights of insufficient sleep can harm heart function.
Early risers may face a higher risk of cardiovascular issues, contrary to popular belief.
Athletes benefit from adequate sleep, improving energy and mood.
Children are increasingly prescribed medication for sleep issues, with little emphasis on behavioral therapy.
Sleep is crucial for memory consolidation, and even one night of poor sleep can impair brain function.
Lack of sleep can also lead to weight gain and increased health risks, emphasizing the importance of quality rest for overall well-being.
